  "What does the term 'standard integral formula' mean?": "",
  "A formula that only applies to polynomial functions": "",
  "A commonly known antiderivative result that serves as a building block for computing more complex integrals": "",
  "The most accurate formula for integration": "",
  "A formula created by a standards organization": "",
  "Standard integral formulas are well-known antiderivative results (like integral of x^n, e^x, sin(x), 1/x, etc.) that are memorized and used as building blocks to evaluate more complex integrals.": "",
  "What does 'simplify before integrating' mean?": "",
  "Algebraically rewriting the integrand into a simpler form before applying integration rules": "",
  "Using numerical methods instead of exact formulas": "",
  "Reducing the limits of integration": "",
  "Removing the constant of integration": "",
  "Simplifying before integrating means rewriting the integrand through algebra (expanding products, dividing terms, factoring) so that standard integration rules can be applied directly to each term.": "",
  "What is a 'logarithmic integral'?": "",
