  "An integral involving log base 10": "",
  "A logarithmic integral arises when integrating 1/x or more generally 1/u where u is a function of x. The result involves the natural logarithm: integral of 1/x dx = ln|x| + C.": "",
  "What does 'term-by-term integration' mean?": "",
  "Integrating one variable at a time in a multivariable function": "",
  "Finding the integral of each factor in a product": "",
  "Integrating each term of a sum or difference separately and combining the results": "",
  "Applying integration by parts to each term": "",
  "Term-by-term integration uses the sum/difference rule to integrate each additive term individually. For example, integral of (x^2 + 3x - 1) dx is computed as integral of x^2 dx + integral of 3x dx - integral of 1 dx.": "",
  "What is the 'linearity of integration'?": "",
