  "The property that all integrals produce linear functions": "",
  "The integral of a linear function is always quadratic": "",
  "The property that integral of [af(x) + bg(x)] dx = a * integral of f(x) dx + b * integral of g(x) dx": "",
  "Linearity of integration means integration distributes over addition and respects scalar multiplication. This fundamental property allows us to break complex integrals into simpler pieces.": "",
  "A water pipe leaks at an increasing rate of L(t) = 0.5t + 2 gallons per hour. If 50 gallons have already leaked when monitoring begins (t = 0), find the total leakage by t = 6 hours.": "",
  "50 gallons": "",
  "71 gallons": "",
  "21 gallons": "",
  "62 gallons": "",
  "W(t) = integral of (0.5t + 2) dt = 0.25t^2 + 2t + C. W(0) = C = 50. W(6) = 0.25(36) + 12 + 50 = 9 + 12 + 50 = 71 gallons.": "",
  "A cyclist accelerates so that their velocity at time t is v(t) = 3t^2 + 2 m/s. If they start at position 10 meters, where are they at t = 3 seconds?": "",
  "33 meters": "",
  "29 meters": "",
  "43 meters": "",
  "37 meters": "",
  "s(t) = integral of (3t^2 + 2) dt = t^3 + 2t + C. s(0) = C = 10. s(3) = 27 + 6 + 10 = 43 meters.": "",
  "An investment earns interest at a rate of I'(t) = 500e^(0.05t) dollars per year. If the initial investment is $10,000, what is the value after 4 years?": "",
  "10000 + 2000 dollars": "",
  "500 e^(0.2) + 10000 dollars": "",
  "10000 * e^(0.2) dollars": "",
  "10000 + 10000(e^(0.2) - 1) dollars": "",
  "I(t) = integral of 500e^(0.05t) dt = 10000e^(0.05t) + C. I(0) = 10000 + C = 10000, so C = 0. Wait, I(0) = 10000(1) + C = 10000 means C = 0. I(4) = 10000e^(0.2). But this gives total as 10000e^(0.2). Actually, the value is V(t) = initial + accumulated interest: integral from 0 to 4 of 500e^(0.05t) dt = 10000(e^(0.2) - 1). Total value = 10000 + 10000(e^(0.2) - 1).": "",
  "A balloon is inflated so that its volume increases at V'(t) = 12 sqrt(t) cm^3/s. If V(0) = 0, find V(9).": "",
  "324 cm^3": "",
  "36 cm^3": "",
  "108 cm^3": "",
  "216 cm^3": "",
  "V(t) = integral of 12t^(1/2) dt = 12 * (2/3)t^(3/2) + C = 8t^(3/2) + C. V(0) = 0, so C = 0. V(9) = 8(27) = 216 cm^3.": "",
  "A student's reading rate is R(t) = 40 - 2t pages per hour. If they have read 120 pages before starting a study session (t = 0), how many total pages have they read after 5 hours?": "",
  "320 pages": "",
  "175 pages": "",
  "295 pages": "",
  "270 pages": "",
  "P(t) = integral of (40 - 2t) dt = 40t - t^2 + C. P(0) = C = 120. P(5) = 200 - 25 + 120 = 295 pages.": "",
  "A radioactive substance decays so that the remaining mass satisfies M'(t) = -0.1e^(-0.1t) grams per year. If M(0) = 1 gram, find M(t).": "",
  "0.1e^(-0.1t) grams": "",
  "-e^(-0.1t) + 2 grams": "",
  "e^(-0.1t) grams": "",
  "1 - 0.1t grams": "",
  "M(t) = integral of -0.1e^(-0.1t) dt = e^(-0.1t) + C. M(0) = 1 + C = 1, so C = 0. Therefore M(t) = e^(-0.1t) grams.": "",
  "A sprinkler rotates and waters an area at rate A'(t) = 2pi * cos(pi*t) square meters per minute. If A(0) = 0, find the area watered at t = 1/2 minute.": "",
  "1 square meter": "",
  "pi square meters": "",
  "2pi square meters": "",
  "2 square meters": "",
  "A(t) = integral of 2pi cos(pi*t) dt = 2pi * (1/pi)sin(pi*t) + C = 2 sin(pi*t) + C. A(0) = 0 + C = 0, so C = 0. A(1/2) = 2 sin(pi/2) = 2 square meters.": "",
  "A dam releases water at rate R(t) = 100/(t+1)^2 thousand gallons per hour. If the reservoir initially holds 500 thousand gallons, how much remains after 4 hours?": "",
  "480 thousand gallons": "",
  "380 thousand gallons": "",
  "400 thousand gallons": "",
  "420 thousand gallons": "",
  "Total released = integral from 0 to 4 of 100/(t+1)^2 dt = [-100/(t+1)] from 0 to 4 = -100/5 + 100/1 = -20 + 100 = 80 thousand gallons. Remaining = 500 - 80 = 420 thousand gallons.": "",
  "A plant grows at height rate h'(t) = 6/(t + 1) cm per week. If the plant is 10 cm tall at t = 0, how tall is it after 3 weeks?": "",
  "16 cm": "",
  "10 + 18 cm": "",
  "10 + 6 ln(3) cm": "",
  "10 + 6 ln(4) cm": "",
  "h(t) = integral of 6/(t+1) dt = 6 ln|t+1| + C. h(0) = 6 ln(1) + C = C = 10. h(3) = 6 ln(4) + 10 = 10 + 6 ln(4) cm.": "",
  "A chemical reaction proceeds at rate r(t) = 8e^(-2t) + 3 mol/min. If the concentration starts at 0, find the total product formed after a very long time (as t approaches infinity).": "",
  "4 + 3 = 7 mol, based on conventional assumptions about": "",
  "4 mol under most circumstances involving approaches": "",
  "The integral diverges (infinite product) due to the constant term": "",
  "11 mol, especially during periods of significant change": "",
  "Integral from 0 to T of (8e^(-2t) + 3) dt = [-4e^(-2t) + 3t] from 0 to T = -4e^(-2T) + 3T + 4. As T approaches infinity, 3T approaches infinity, so the integral diverges. The constant production rate of 3 mol/min accumulates without bound.": ""
